usage: interf_sample.py [-h] [-loc LOCATION] [-lt LAT] [-lg LON]
                        [-ra RIGHTASCENTION] [-dec DECLINATION] [-c]
                        [-cb CELESTIALBODY] [-dt TRACKDURATION] [-t]

Program used to capture data via digital sampling

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -loc LOCATION, --location LOCATION
                        [string] enter location instead of lat, lon. Format:
                        'address, city, state', e.g., 'University Dr.,
                        Berkeley, CA'
  -lt LAT, --lat LAT    [float] takes in latitude
  -lg LON, --lon LON    [float] takes in longitude
  -ra RIGHTASCENTION, --rightascention RIGHTASCENTION
                        [float] take in right ascention
  -dec DECLINATION, --declination DECLINATION
                        [float] take in declination
  -c, --capture         captures data
  -cb CELESTIALBODY, --celestialbody CELESTIALBODY
                        [string] input specific celestial body [sun, moon]
  -dt TRACKDURATION, --trackduration TRACKDURATION
                        [int] sets time to track for
  -t, --time            prints the current time. Unix, utc, and local system
                        time.
